public class NEATReproductionStrategyImpl
extends AbstractNEATReproductionStrategy<GeneMap>

NEATReproductionStrategyImpl implements the NEATReproductionStrategy interface for use with NEATGenomes with a data payload of type GeneMap. It orchestrates the creation of child genomes, selecting which genomes will reproduce and via which of MutateOperator or CrossoverOperator.

Calls to AbstractNEATReproductionStrategy.generateChildren(Population) ignore the given count, instead producing from each species a number of children determined by that species number of elites and it's target size. Also, when using a CrossoverOperator, with a certain probability (specified by NEATEvolutionFieldMap.interspeciesCrossoverProbability()) a genome may reproduce with another in a different species.

The NEATReproductionStrategy with attempt to create children until the requested count has been reached; if no operator with succeed with any genome, the method will loop. It's recommended to use at least one Operator that will always succeed, e.g., CopyMutateOperator or CopyCrossoverOperator.

Author:
Luis Guimbarda
